item.title: What song got you into what genre?
item.dc:creator: Slash
item.description:
Sorry for the revive, but, I had a few answers for this one.

WARNING: This list is gonna be a little long, because I like a lot of music genres, and not all of them are electronic. I’ll start with the non electronic ones first.

Rock (in general): Queen- Bohemian Rhapsody
Emo: My Chemical Romance- The Ghost Of You
Punk: Green Day- American Idiot
Southern Rock: Lynyrd Skynyrd- Sweet Home Alabama
Country: Rascal Flatts- Life Is A Highway (I love the Cars movies)
Rap: 50 Cent- In Da Club
————————————
Now for the electronic songs that got me into that genre

Electronic Music (in general): Martin Garrix- Animals

Big Room: Martin Garrix- Animals
Electro House: Zedd- Spectrum
Progressive House: Deadmau5- Faxing Berlin
Bass House: Slushii (yes, he produces bass house) & Holly- All Night Long
Future House: Oliver Heldens- Gecko
Future Bounce: Justin Mylo- Jumping Jack
Trance: Tiesto- Adagio For Strings
Dubstep: Skrillex- Scary Monsters And Nice Sprites
Future Bass: Marshmello- Summer
Trap: DJ Snake and Lil Jon- Turn Down For What
Electronic Pop: Porter Robinson’s Worlds Album
Vaporwave: SAINT PEPSI- ENJOY YOURSELF
Retrowave- @stereofield -Awaken
Moombahton: Dillon Francis- LGFD
Drum And Bass: @Octave- Immersion
Hardstyle: High Voltage- Bombs Away

item.title: What song got you into what genre?
item.dc:creator: Eswyn
item.description:
Shelter (Porter Robinson and Madeon), Sad Machine (Actually just Porter Robinson in general), and some of Snail’s House’s stuff (Specifically Pixel Dream) got me off of my straight 128bpm 4 on the floor dance beat stuff I was writing. I had trouble coming up with different and unique ideas. I’ve been listening to a lot more variety of Ambient and Future Bass-y kind of stuff more recently. I’ve been experimenting with lots of new styles and bpms - I’m just evolving my stuff and finding new things I like/am good at. Not sure about any specific tracks though, but I’ve also been delving into Ambient and Orchestral (I’ve always had a love for the Minecraft soundtrack over the years, so I feel like that might play a role into it.) Pretty much every deadmau5 song is what got me into progressive house and deep house originally.
